President Joe Biden has announced his intent to nominate Charlie Crist as the Representative of the United States of America on the Council of the International Civil Aviation Organization. Crist is a political leader and attorney who has dedicated his life to public service. He previously served as a U.S. Congressman, the Governor of Florida, the state's Attorney General, and the Commissioner of Education. During his time as Governor, Crist guided the state through challenging times such as the Great Recession and the Deepwater Horizon oil spill. He prioritized public education and worked to secure funding to save teachers' jobs. He is also an environmental advocate and has worked to secure aid for the restoration of the Florida Everglades. Crist began his political career in the Florida State Senate and holds a Juris Doctorate degree from Cumberland School of Law.

President Biden also intends to nominate Michael Colin Casey as the Director of the National Counterintelligence and Security Center. Casey currently serves as the Staff Director for the Senate Select Committee on Intelligence. In this role, he oversees the committee staff and assists in conducting oversight of the Intelligence Community's operations. He has over 27 years of experience on Capitol Hill, with a focus on national security. Casey holds a degree from the University of Kentucky and an M.A. from Georgetown University.